{{Infobox company | name = Design International | logo = Design International Logo.png | logo_size = | type = Private Company | foundation = 1965 | founder = Paul Mollé | location = [[London]], United Kingdom | locations = Present in 45 countries | key_people = [[Davide Padoa]] (CEO) | industry = [[Architecture]], design and engineering | products = | services = Consultancy services | slogan = | revenue = | operating_income = | net_income = | num_employees = | subsid = | homepage = [http://www.designinternational.com/ www.designinternational.com] }}
'''Design International''' is an international architectural firm, which was founded in [[Toronto]] in 1965. The firm initially operated mainly in the North American market, but has since developed into a major international player{{citation needed|date=June 2015}} and was one of the first architecture companies that truly worked on a global scale.{{citation needed|date=June 2015}} Today, the company's headquarters are in [[London]], with subsidiary offices in Milan, Shanghai, Jakarta and recently open in Dubai.
Design International works across 7 integrated divisions: Architecture, Masterplanning, Interior Design, Lighting Design, Landscape Design, Branding & Signage, and Leasing.<ref>{{cite web|title=About Design International|url=http://www.designinternational.com/services}}</ref> The company is run by CEO [[Davide Padoa]].
The firm's portfolio includes a number of award-winning developments,<ref>{{cite web|title=MAPIC Awards 2012|url=http://www.mapic.com/RM/RM_MIPIM_v2/documents/pdf/mapic/mapic2012-awards-winners.pdf}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Global RLI Awards 2012|url=http://www.rli.uk.com/awards/2012/}}</ref> especially in the retail and entertainment sector, such as [[CocoWalk]] (1990), an upscale [[lifestyle center]] in the Coconut Grove neighborhood of Miami, Florida; Odysseum (2009), a retail and entertainment complex in Montpellier, France; and the iconic [[Morocco Mall]] (2011), Africa's largest destination mall located on the [[Casablanca]] beach front promenade. The mall also includes one of only four [[Galeries Lafayette]] stores outside France.
More recently, in 2014, the firm completed Nave de Vero<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://corrieredelveneto.corriere.it/veneto/notizie/cronaca/2014/25-marzo-2014/approda-marghera-nave-de-vero-centro-commerciale-ecocompatibile-2224265528789.shtml?refresh_ce-cp|title=A Marghera il centro commerciale ecocompatibile la|work=Corriere del Veneto|access-date=2018-02-12|language=it-IT}}</ref>, which is located in Venice, Italy. The concept behind Nave de Vero is based on Venice’s merchant trading history. The project has won many awards, and in November 2014, was awarded a [[BREEAM]] rating of ‘Very Good’.<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.designinternational.com/nave-de-vero-becomes-first-commercial-retail-project-italy-obtain-breeam-certificate|title = Nave de Vero receives BREEAM rating of 'Very Good'|date = November 2014|accessdate = |website = Nave de Vero receives BREEAM rating of 'Very Good'|publisher = |last = Mifsud|first = Rebecca}}</ref> This achievement makes the shopping centre the first commercial project in Italy to achieve this certification.{{citation needed|date=June 2015}}
Design International is also responsible for the Cleopatra Mall<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.arch2o.com/cleopatra-mall-design-international/|title=Cleopatra Mall {{!}} Design International - Arch2O.com|date=2017-05-20|work=Arch2O.com|access-date=2018-02-12|language=en-US}}</ref>, which is due to open in 2017, in [[Cairo]], Egypt. The shopping mall, which is currently under construction, is characterised by a gigantic canopy covering the central area of the scheme with a span of over 200 metres. The project includes over 300 shops and restaurants, and is set to include an outdoor musical fountain, gourmet markets and Egypt’s first dedicated luxury mall inside a shopping centre.{{citation needed|date=June 2015}}
In 2015, Design International announced their involvement in the [http://www.designinternational.com/design-international-create-destination-mall-part-king%E2%80%99s-%E2%80%98royal-vision%E2%80%99-morocco-0 ‘Wessal Bouregreg]’ <ref>{{Cite news|url = http://www.designinternational.com/design-international-create-destination-mall-part-king%E2%80%99s-%E2%80%98royal-vision%E2%80%99-morocco-0|title = Design International to create a destination mall as part of the King’s ‘Royal Vision’ for Morocco|last = Mifsud|first = Rebecca|date = March 2015|work = |access-date = |via = }}</ref> project in Rabat which is part of the King of Morocco's ‘Royal Vision’ for making Morocco an international destination.
The summer of 2015 also marked the moving of Design International’s London headquarters to a new location in Bermondsey.
